An APRA-regulated institution's risk management framework must, at a minimum, include:

(a) a risk appetite statement;
(b) an RMS (Risk Management Strategy);
(c) a business plan;
(d) policies and procedures supporting clearly defined and documented roles, responsibilities and formal reporting structures for the management of material risks throughout the institution;
(e) a designated risk management function that meets the requirements of paragraph 37;
(f) an Internal Capital Adequacy Assessment Process (ICAAP);
(g) a management information system (MIS) that is adequate, both under normal circumstances and in periods of stress, for measuring, assessing and reporting on all material risks across the institution; and
(h) a review process to ensure that the risk management framework is effective in identifying, measuring, evaluating, monitoring, reporting, and controlling or mitigating material risks [cps220 | 23].

