An APRA-regulated institution's risk management framework must, at a minimum, address the following material risks under CPS 220:

(a) credit risk;
(b) market and investment risk;
(c) liquidity risk;
(d) insurance risk;
(e) operational risk;
(f) risks arising from the strategic objectives and business plans; and
(g) other risks that, singly or in combination with different risks, may have a material impact on the institution [KG-EXPANDED | cps220 | 26].

Under section 916A of the Corporations Act 2001, a financial services licensee's authorisation of a representative is void to the extent that it purports to authorise a person to provide a financial service that is:

(a) not covered by the licensee's licence;

(b) contrary to a banning order or disqualification order under Division 8;

(c) in contravention of subsection 921C(2) [corporations_act_2001 | 916A(3)].

An APRA-regulated entity’s BCP must include the following under CPS 230:

(a) the register of critical operations and associated tolerance levels;
(b) triggers to identify a disruption and prompt activation of the plan, and arrangements to direct resources in the event of activation;
(c) actions it would take to maintain its critical operations within tolerance levels through disruptions;
(d) an assessment of the execution risks, required resources, preparatory measures, including key internal and external dependencies needed to support the effective implementation of the BCP actions; and
(e) a communications strategy to support execution of the plan [cps230 | 40].

